================ OVERVIEW ================


Unicast Flooding is a switch's response to a unicast frame when the destination is unknown,
whereas Broadcast is a deliberate communication to all devices within a broadcast domain.


By now it should be clear that VLANs and multiple Switches behave differently.
   - VLANs are based on the same switch, logically dividing itself.
       - VLANs cannot communicate with each other.
       - Unless other Layer 3 devices (Routers) are introduced.
   - Multiple switches are physically divided. They are different devices.
       - If there are multiple switches on the same network like shown above in Multiple Switches Network,
         every host in that network can communicate with one another.

